{{nihongo|'''Nomi no Sukune'''|野見 宿禰}} was a Japanese legendary [[sumo]] wrestler during [[Emperor Suinin]] era. He kicked and killed his opponent Taima no Kehaya (当麻蹴速) under Emperor's instruction. It wasn't modern sumo, but he is regarded as the human creator of sumo. He was an ancestor of [[Sugawara no Michizane]].

